FP.CPI.TOTL-hc.def: Consumer price index reflects changes in the cost to the average consumer of acquiring a basket of goods and services that may be fixed or changed at specified intervals, such as yearly. The Laspeyres formula is generally used. Data are period averages.
FP.CPI.TOTL-hc.name: Consumer price index
FP.CPI.TOTL-hc.source: International Monetary Fund, International Financial Statistics and data files.

FP.CPI.TOTL.ZG-hc.def: Inflation as measured by the consumer price index reflects the annual percentage change in the cost to the average consumer of acquiring a basket of goods and services that may be fixed or changed at specified intervals, such as yearly. The Laspeyres formula is generally used.
FP.CPI.TOTL.ZG-hc.name: Inflation
FP.CPI.TOTL.ZG-hc.source: International Monetary Fund, International Financial Statistics and data files.

FP.WPI.TOTL-hc.def: Wholesale price index refers to a mix of agricultural and industrial goods at various stages of production and distribution, including import duties. The Laspeyres formula is generally used.
FP.WPI.TOTL-hc.name: Wholesale price index
FP.WPI.TOTL-hc.source: International Monetary Fund, International Financial Statistics and data files.

NY.GDP.DEFL.KD.ZG-hc.def: Inflation as measured by the annual growth rate of the GDP implicit deflator shows the rate of price change in the economy as a whole. The GDP implicit deflator is the ratio of GDP in current local currency to GDP in constant local currency.
NY.GDP.DEFL.KD.ZG-hc.name: Inflation
NY.GDP.DEFL.KD.ZG-hc.source: World Bank national accounts data, and OECD National Accounts data files.

NY.GDP.DEFL.KD.ZG.AD-hc.def: Inflation as measured by the annual growth rate of the GDP implicit deflator shows the rate of price change in the economy as a whole. This series has been linked to produce a consistent time series to counteract breaks in series over time due to changes in base years, source data and methodologies. Thus, it may not be comparable with other national accounts series in the database for historical years.
NY.GDP.DEFL.KD.ZG.AD-hc.name: Inflation, GDP deflator: linked series
NY.GDP.DEFL.KD.ZG.AD-hc.source: World Bank staff estimates based on World Bank national accounts data archives, OECD National Accounts, and the IMF WEO database.

NY.GDP.DEFL.ZS-hc.def: The GDP implicit deflator is the ratio of GDP in current local currency to GDP in constant local currency. The base year varies by country.
NY.GDP.DEFL.ZS-hc.name: GDP deflator
NY.GDP.DEFL.ZS-hc.source: World Bank national accounts data, and OECD National Accounts data files.

NY.GDP.DEFL.ZS.AD-hc.def: The GDP implicit deflator is calculated as the ratio of GDP in current local currency to GDP in constant local currency. This series has been linked to produce a consistent time series to counteract breaks in series over time due to changes in base years, source data and methodologies. Thus, it may not be comparable with other national accounts series in the database for historical years. The base year varies by country.
NY.GDP.DEFL.ZS.AD-hc.name: GDP deflator
NY.GDP.DEFL.ZS.AD-hc.source: World Bank staff estimates based on World Bank national accounts data archives, OECD National Accounts, and the IMF WEO database.

PA.NUS.ATLS-hc.def: The DEC alternative conversion factor is the underlying annual exchange rate used for the World Bank Atlas method. As a rule, it is the official exchange rate reported in the IMF's International Financial Statistics (line rf). Exceptions arise where further refinements are made by World Bank staff. It is expressed in local currency units per U.S. dollar.
PA.NUS.ATLS-hc.name: DEC alternative conversion factor
PA.NUS.ATLS-hc.source: International Monetary Fund, International Financial Statistics, supplemented by World Bank staff estimates.

PA.NUS.FCRF-hc.def: Official exchange rate refers to the exchange rate determined by national authorities or to the rate determined in the legally sanctioned exchange market. It is calculated as an annual average based on monthly averages (local currency units relative to the U.S. dollar).
PA.NUS.FCRF-hc.name: Official exchange rate
PA.NUS.FCRF-hc.source: International Monetary Fund, International Financial Statistics.

PX.REX.REER-hc.def: Real effective exchange rate is the nominal effective exchange rate (a measure of the value of a currency against a weighted average of several foreign currencies) divided by a price deflator or index of costs.
PX.REX.REER-hc.name: Real effective exchange rate index
PX.REX.REER-hc.source: International Monetary Fund, International Financial Statistics.
